# Scroll Showcase Rule

## Triggers

Use this rule when a user asks for a Raycast-style website, Apple-style showcase, NVIDIA-style reveal, RTX/GPU page, scroll parallax page, sticky scroll website, pinned product reveal, animated SaaS landing page, app showcase, AI browser landing page, or premium product storytelling page.

## Files To Read

1. `skills/monich/SKILL.md`
2. Read and recursively scan the whole `templates/` folder.
3. If present, scan every folder and file inside `templates/web-template/design-templates/`, `templates/web-template/horizontal-craft/`, and `templates/web-template/design-systems/`.
4. Read actual source/reference files inside every template/reference folder, including `.html`, `.css`, `.js`, `.jsx`, `.tsx`, `.md`, `.json`, and design-token files. Do not rely only on `SKILL.md`, `README.md`, `info.md`, or folder names.
5. Build an inventory of template names, metadata, visual style, page type, layout pattern, motion pattern, component language, color system, typography, and stack.
6. For broad or style-sensitive requests, show the user 2-4 closest template references with a short rationale before implementation.
7. Choose the closest matching template or reference set from that inventory.

## Implementation Rules

- Generate complete runnable code.
- Default to React for generated websites.
- Use React + Vite for fast demos and React + Next.js when the user asks for Next.js or the project already uses it.
- Adapt to Astro, SvelteKit, Vue, Nuxt, or another framework when requested.
- Use the stack requested by the user, the existing project, or the template scan.
- Use sticky sections with tall wrappers from 250vh to 500vh.
- Keep a single main focal object.
- Build layered depth: background, glow/grid, midground cards, product mockup, foreground text.
- Use CSS-only app/product mockups if no assets are provided.
- Animate transform and opacity by default.
- Add responsive layouts and mobile fallbacks.
- Add `prefers-reduced-motion` CSS.
- Keep imports and dependencies exact.
- Learn from template structure, visual systems, motion timing, and component patterns.
- Do not default back to starter-template visuals when a closer `web-template` reference exists.
- If implementing in React, Next.js, or another framework, translate the selected `web-template` style into that stack.
- Do not copy-paste template code line-by-line into the generated project.
- Write fresh components, styles, content, and data for the target stack.
- Match visible copy to the language the user spoke.
- If a web-template reference contains Chinese, rewrite the generated page copy into the user's language unless Chinese was requested.
- Set `<html lang>` or framework metadata to the content language.

## Forbidden Patterns

- Do not copy Raycast, NVIDIA, Apple, or any real brand.
- Do not use their assets, logos, screenshots, product names, claims, or exact layouts.
- Do not invent missing assets.
- Do not ship a copied template with only text or color substitutions.
- Do not produce the starter-template look after selecting a richer `web-template` reference.
- Do not leave Chinese placeholder copy in non-Chinese user requests.
- Do not animate layout properties such as top, left, width, height, margin, or padding.
- Do not create generic neon AI SaaS slop or particle-heavy backgrounds.

## Quality Checklist

- App runs with the documented command.
- Sticky or pinned scroll scene works.
- Scroll wrapper has enough height.
- Main product/app mockup is visible.
- Mobile layout remains readable.
- Reduced motion keeps content accessible.
- No missing imports.
- No unused packages.
- No brand assets copied.
